$interpreted: Pious Commoner: The Blessing Ceremony is going to start!
Excited Commoner: I'm so excited~ With the High Priest's blessings, may the grace of the Snake God be with us always!
Religious Cleric: High Priest, the last batch of people who have come to see the ceremony have entered the New City.
Pious Commoner: May the Snake God bless the Holy Maiden Misa! Bless the High Priest Devious!
Excited Commoner: Misa, I love you!
Devious: Citizens of the Desert Kingdom, friends from afar~
Devious: Today is the sacred Blessing Ceremony. I have poured all my energy into this day, toiling over this plan——
Devious: and finally, it is time to reap the harvest!
Pious Commoner: Merciful Snake God!!
Devious: Ages ago, on this day, the Snake God and Goddess sacrificed themselves for the citizens of the Desert Kingdom and for hundreds of years of prosperity.
Devious: All here today are incarnations of their flesh and blood, piously attending this ceremony. I presume all of you have prepared with full devotion.
Pious Commoner: Holy Maiden Misa! Holy Maiden Misa! Holy Maiden Misa!
Misa: ...High Priest Devious?
Devious: The greatest bliss does indeed come to those who are ignorant. But I'm afraid you've been mistaken~
Devious: The one whom you must devote yourself to...hssssss...is none other than...
Devious: Me!
Devious: I will replace Sdorica and become the new god of this world.
Devious: In order to complete this enormous task, I must ask all of you...to become fodder for me, your god!
Misa: Sdorica! Isn't that the name of the heretics false god!?
Misa: High Priest Devious, even though it is you, to speak such blasphemy during the Blessing Ceremony is unforgivable!
Misa: ...*wince*...I'm bleeding...
Misa: Hmph, it's just a small wound. As long as the Snake Goddess——
Misa: ...I can't cast my powers?
Devious: Poor child, you thought the power was yours?
Misa: What?
Devious: Holy Maiden, today's medicine tasted different, didn't it? It's no surprise you have so much energy today, wouldn't you say?
Misa: ...You're right...
Devious: The medicine that you take every day I made with my own hands. It gives you the ability to heal others, but it also weakens you even further.
Devious: This Holy Maiden, mystical powers nonsense...it's all fake.
Devious: I used the orphanage you came from to carry out experiments on snakes.
Devious: The other orphans simply couldn't adapt to the medicine. Your physique is unique, so you were able to survive. That's all.
Misa: But...you said I was the Snake Goddess incarnate...
Devious: A lie told to children. Of course, only a child would believe it. Snake God?
Devious: The Rib of the Snake God which you worship is nothing more than the tooth of Sdorica!
Devious: There's never been a Snake God or Goddess. It's all just religious nonsense, made up to trick you foolish idiots.
Misa: No...I don't believe...it can't be...
Devious: You fraud, you don't even know what you believe. Does it even matter if you believe what I say?
Devious: Awaken, Dragon Tooth!
